        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 2 at 2:21PM EST by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM EST/121 PM CST/, the public reported showers over Signal
Mountain, or 9 miles northwest of Chattanooga, moving north at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Dunlap, Jasper, Soddy-Daisy, Signal Mountain, South
Pittsburg, Walden, Lakesite, Whitwell, and Kimball.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
